	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sorry fot the Off-Topic, but I've seen this operand many times, but never seen what is it for in any tutorial or doc: #&gt; and #&lt;
<br />
<br />like in this lines:<div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">adc #&lt;addr<br />lda #&gt;addr </div>
<br />
<br />I think I also saw it with indirect addressing, something like &lt;(some_addr) but I'm not sure.
<br />
<br />What's it for?

		

		</td>
